org.openmuc.iec62056.data

Class IdentificationMessage

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.openmuc.iec62056.data.IdentificationMessage

  • public class IdentificationMessage
extends java.lang.Object
    Format: '/' X X X Z Identification 'CR' 'LF'

    X X X = manufacturer identification (three characters)

    Z = baud rate identification, is also used to select the mode, e.g. if Z='A'...'F' then mode B is selected

    Identification = manufacturer specific device ID that has a maximum length of 16. It may contain the escape character '\' followed by W which is the enhanced baud rate and mode identification character.
